s well as the self-deceptive aspects of Modern poetry. This book alters our understanding of the history of poetry in the English language.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEnglish languagexStyle. 0aEnglish poetryy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 70(DE-601)1041377890(DE-588)4036774-5aLyrik2gnd 70(DE-601)1046587110(DE-588)4039827-4aModerne2gnd 70(DE-601)1056873910(DE-588)4132483-3aSprachstil2gnd 70(DE-601)1063387490(DE-588)4014777-0aEnglisch2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010071640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012948940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300129489423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300129489/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY